   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="edition">
            <ab>
               <lb n="1"/>
               <persName>
                  <name type="praenomen" key="Lucius">
                     <expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>ucius</ex></expan>
                  </name>
                  <name type="gentilicium"><abbr>C</abbr></name>
                  <name type="cognomen"><abbr><hi rend="ligature">MY</hi></abbr></name>
               </persName>
            </ab>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>Stamp of Lucius C( ) My( ).</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The Harvard Art Museums record describes the inscription as LCMY and notes the frequent ligature of MY, where the lower stroke of the Y forms the final side stroke of the M. The name of L. C( ) My( ) is not securely expandable. Parallels are reported from Rome, Britain, and Germania; a complete globular amphora bearing a related stamp makes a southern Spanish origin likely.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="apparatus">
